# Color System Rules

This project uses ONLY black, white, and gray shades as its color palette.
All color decisions must use CSS variables defined in `theme.css` at the project root.

## Allowed tokens

- `var(--color-black)` → #000000
- `var(--color-white)` → #ffffff
- `var(--color-gray-50)` through `var(--color-gray-900)` for all shading needs

## Semantic aliases to use in components

- `var(--color-bg)` — page background
- `var(--color-bg-subtle)` — subtle section backgrounds
- `var(--color-surface)` — card/panel surfaces
- `var(--color-border)` — borders and dividers
- `var(--color-text)` — primary text
- `var(--color-text-muted)` — secondary/muted text
- `var(--color-text-faint)` — placeholder/disabled text

## Forbidden

- Never use named colors: red, blue, green, yellow, etc.
- Never hardcode hex values except #000, #fff, #000000, #ffffff
- Never use rgba() with any values other than 0,0,0 or 255,255,255
- Never use Tailwind color utilities like `text-blue-500`, `bg-red-400`, `border-green-200`
- The files `globals.css` and `dashboard.css` must also follow these rules

## Handling states without color

- Hover: change `background` using a gray token, not a colored one
- Focus: use `outline: var(--border-width-thick) solid var(--color-black)`
- Error: use bold border + an icon or text label — NOT red text or red borders
- Disabled: apply `opacity: 0.4` to the element
- Active/selected: use `background: var(--color-black)` with `color: var(--color-white)`
